Assessment of residual mediastinal tumor in patients with Hodgkin's lymphoma using computed tomography, magnetic resonance and 67Ga scintigraphy. 594 patients with Hodgkin's disease were treated from 1983 to 1993 at the Department of Radiotherapy and Institute of Hematology, "La Sapienza" University, Rome, Italy. 385 patients presented mediastinal involvement CT and/or chest radiography showed residual mediastinal masses in 96 of them (25%). In this study we included only the patients treated after 1986